  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Disaster Prevention by Improving Irrigation and Water Resource Management at the Community Level</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project has three key areas of implementation. The first area of intervention is in disaster risk mitigation (DRM) infrastructure via the construction of small-scale disaster mitigation infrastructure and water irrigation systems. The second area of intervention is in community-based DRM in which communities are trained to mitigate and prepare for the effects of natural disasters. The third area of intervention is in capacity building and technical support to the Afghanistan National Disaster Management Authority&apos;s (ANDMA) National Disaster Management Information System (NDMIS) by supporting a functional NDMIS system operating in all provinces adapted to its needs and capacities to result in enhanced and timely information management. This activity seeks to enable provincial and headquarters ANDMA staff to successfully use the NDMIS and obtain timely information on natural disaster affected or displaced population to better coordinate natural disaster incidents, conduct timely assessments, and provide a coordinated response.</narrative>
  </description>
